cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper discusses the use of neural networks to learn genomic representations for predicting patient survival in cancer. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of neural networks also suggests the possibility of computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) techniques being employed. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of deep learning (cs.NE) methods, further supporting the likelihood of it belonging to these sub-categories.
